<div class="modal fade" id="inventoryBulkHelpModal" tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="inventoryBulkHelpModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg modal-dialog-scrollable">
        <div class="modal-content">
            <div class="modal-header">
                <div>
                    <h5 class="modal-title" id="inventoryBulkHelpModalLabel">How to Use Bulk Update</h5>
                    <div class="text-muted small">A quick walkthrough for updating many inventory items without editing every card one by one.</div>
                </div>
                <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
                <ul class="inventory-bulk-help-list">
                    <li>
                        <h6>1. Choose what items you want to affect</h6>
                        <p class="mb-2">Use the page filters first if you want to narrow the list by character, item type, or name. Then choose a bulk scope:</p>
                        <p class="mb-1"><strong>Filtered results</strong> updates everything that currently matches your filters.</p>
                        <p class="mb-1"><strong>Current page</strong> updates only the visible page of cards.</p>
                        <p><strong>Selected items</strong> updates only the cards whose checkboxes you turned on.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <h6>2. Use selection when you want extra control</h6>
                        <p class="mb-2">Each card has a checkbox in the top-right corner. This is the safest option when you only want to change a handful of items.</p>
                        <p class="mb-1">Use <strong>Select Current Page</strong> to quickly mark every card you can currently see.</p>
                        <p>Use <strong>Clear Selection</strong> if you want to start over.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <h6>3. Apply one type of change at a time</h6>
                        <p class="mb-2">Pick the change you want, then click <strong>Apply</strong>.</p>
                        <p class="mb-1"><strong>Weapon ownership</strong> changes ownership status like 5 Star or OB10.</p>
                        <p class="mb-1"><strong>Weapon level</strong> sets the stored level for owned weapons.</p>
                        <p class="mb-1"><strong>Costume ownership</strong> marks costumes as own or do not own.</p>
                        <p class="mb-0"><strong>Clear Weapon Levels</strong> removes saved levels but keeps ownership. <strong>Reset Scope to Do Not Own</strong> clears ownership in the chosen scope.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <h6>4. Use Paste Import when you already have a list</h6>
                        <p class="mb-2">The <strong>Paste Import</strong> button is useful when you copied rows from notes or a spreadsheet.</p>
                        <p class="mb-1">You can paste CSV, TSV, or simple lines like <code>Murasame - OB10 - 140</code>.</p>
                        <p class="mb-1">Click <strong>Parse Rows</strong> first to preview matches, warnings, and skipped rows.</p>
                        <p>Nothing changes until you click <strong>Apply Import</strong>.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <h6>5. Pick the right import mode</h6>
                        <p class="mb-1"><strong>Merge matched rows</strong> updates matched items with the values you provided.</p>
                        <p class="mb-1"><strong>Only fill blanks / unowned entries</strong> avoids overwriting items you already filled in.</p>
                        <p><strong>Replace matched rows</strong> is the strongest option and can clear existing stored levels if your pasted replacement row leaves level blank.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <h6>6. If something looks wrong, use Undo</h6>
                        <p class="mb-0">After a bulk action or paste import, use <strong>Undo Last Bulk Update</strong> right away if you need to roll it back. It only keeps the most recent bulk-style change, so it is best used immediately.</p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-footer">
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-bs-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="modal fade" id="pasteImportModal" tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="pasteImportModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
